The First Lady, Jill Biden, spoke at the Marriott Marquis in Washington, D.C. She expressed her condolences for a school shooting that had just occurred in Tennessee and emphasized the need for better protection for children. She praised local leaders for their ability to find common ground and serve their communities. Biden discussed the importance of education and jobs, specifically focusing on community colleges and career training programs. She highlighted various examples of successful partnerships between schools and businesses that provide students with valuable skills for the workforce. Biden encouraged local leaders to reimagine what is possible in their communities and work together to create opportunities for students. She emphasized that the Biden administration is committed to supporting education and career pathways.